main event: A radar observation of a disk-shaped, yellowish object was recorded in Dayton, Ohio on 9 October 1953.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 33 seconds and included radar ground observations., The object was described as disk-shaped and moved west before turning south and disappearing behind clouds., The object was observed using ground radar and air interceptor radar., The case classified the object as unknown, possibly due to a balloon or aircraft., No photographs were included in the report.
